    "bill"
  ],
  "subject": [
    "Alcoholanddrugtreatmentfacilities"
  ],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "Existing law requires the State Department of Health Care Services to license and regulate facilities that provide residential nonmedical services to adults who are recovering from problems related to alcohol, drug, or alcohol and drug misuse or abuse, and who need alcohol, drug, or alcohol and drug recovery treatment or detoxification services. Violation of licensing provisions is punishable through revocation or suspension of the license and civil penalties.\n\nThis bill would prohibit an alcohol or other drug recovery or treatment facility from operating within 1,000 feet of a public or private elementary or secondary school or a daycare center if the recovery or treatment facility serves more than 6 residents and treatment is being provided at the facility.\n\nThis bill would declare that it is to take effect immediately as an urgency statute."
    }
  ],
